  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6772.41 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6770 (-38B) and positive gamma wall at 6800 (+48.6B), dealers are likely moderately buying the current dip as we're below the flip at 6807 but above the major amplifying level. The PIN regime with massive 47.7B total GEX suggests strong mean-reversion forces, with dealers expected to provide significant buying support into any move toward 6770 and selling pressure into rallies toward 6800. Watch 6770 closely as a break below triggers amplified selling from dealers, while 6800 represents the key resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect bouncy action between 6770-6800 with limited breakout potential.",
